data.title: Maksim Chmerkovskiy and Peta Murgatroyd Enjoy 'Parents Night Out,' Pack on the PDA: Pics!
data.meta_description: Maksim Chmerkovskiy and Peta Murgatroyd look more in love than ever.
data.text:
Maksim Chmerkovskiy and Peta Murgatroyd have the look of love!

The couple spent a night out in New York City sans their 1-month-old son, Shai, on Thursday, to support Maksim's younger brother, Val Chmerkovskiy. Maksim and Peta attended Val's fashion show for his clothing line with former Dancing With the Stars troupe member Nicole Volynet, VALENTINNICOLE, which showed during New York Fashion Week.

The two weren't shy about showing lots of PDA at the event, Maksim sweetly kissing his fiancee on the cheek.

WATCH: Peta Murgatroyd Gets Real About Her Post-Baby Bod, Enjoys 'First Date Night of 2017' With Maksim Chmerkovskiy

Getty Images

The 37-year-old pro dancer was also snapped looking adoringly at Peta.

Getty Images

Clearly, Maks appears to be more smitten with 30-year-old Peta than ever.

"Hottest chick in the spot!" he Instagrammed alongside a pic of Peta at the show. "That line next to the corner of the lip is my absolute favorite... #queen."

Meanwhile, Peta shared her own photo of the attractive couple, calling their outing "Parents night out."

The two have found some alone time to spend together apart from son Shai in NYC. Earlier this week, Peta shared a makeup-free Instagram photo of her and her man taking a car ride. "Typical, he's always on the phone while I'm trying to take a selfie #manhattanday away from #babychmerkovskiy," she joked.

Though both Maks and Peta are definitely loving their new role in life. Last week, Maks Instagrammed a sweet video of Peta checking on their son.

"Never heard 'Wait, I'm checking on my baby,' right before a dance, but something about @petamurgatroyd saying it makes me very happy," he wrote.

WATCH: Maksim Chmerkovskiy Reflects on Fatherhood -- 'I'm the Happiest Person That's Ever Lived'

Peta gave birth to their first child together on Jan. 4. Last month, Val said being a father has "changed" his brother during an appearance on Good Morning America.

"I'm trying to be the best uncle I can be," Val added. "I want to spoil him. I don't think he really understands much right now. But as soon as he's able to comprehend the love that he has around him, I think he's going to be a very spoiled young man."
